        <title>A Vision for Your Program</title>
        <contents>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Listen to audio:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/ELL_Mod3_2210.mp3"&gt;ELL_Mod3_2210.mp3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;details&gt;&lt;summary&gt;Audio transcript&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Deeper Learning Model is receiving a lot of attention in K-12 education but its approach has merit for Adult Education as well. The graphic represents its Theory of Action and highlights (1) the need for a strong school culture and (2) a professional learning community that includes teachers. It also emphasizes the importance of creating meaningful learning experiences (3) and of focusing on outcomes that capture meaningful learning that goes beyond knowing facts and using lower level cognitive skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now think about your own situation and create a sketch of your vision for a high quality program for English learners preparing for work and transition to career pathways. What components do you need to consider that affect the success of such a program? What role might your partners play? How do you see support services and advising fit into the picture?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/details&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Deeper%20Learning.png" width="501" height="760" alt="Deeper Learning Graphic showing four components of the Theory of Action" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;As illustrated in the infographic, the four components of deeper learning are:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Create a strong &lt;span style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;school culture&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Teachers function as professionals in a &lt;span style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;collaborative community&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Teachers design &lt;span style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;meaningful learning experiences&lt;/span&gt; for students:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Students demonstrate the mastery of knowledge and skills&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Learning is related to real life.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Learning is aligned to standards and deeper learning outcomes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Learning has coherence and meaning.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Deliberate practice of &lt;span style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;deeper learning outcomes&lt;/span&gt; for students:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Work collaboratively&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Academic mindset&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Learning to learn&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Master core knowledge&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Communicate effectively&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Think critically and solve complex problems&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;The result of deeper learning is students leave school with how, when, and why to apply skills and knowledge to face challenges of college, career, and life.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium; line-height: 1.231;"&gt;The new direction toward a greater emphasis on skills related to work and careers also offers opportunities to reconceptualize ELA services.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Think about the changes you envision making that will transform your program, engage teachers and staff, and broaden the employment prospects for students. How can you create a culture of learning for your entire program and how can you involve other partners to make your program a success?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</contents>
